continuous-integration.md
     1‚Üí# Running `mdbook` in continuous integration
     3‚ÜíThere are a variety of services such as [GitHub Actions] or [GitLab CI/CD] which can be used to test and deploy your book automatically.
     4‚Üí
     5‚ÜíThe following provides some general guidelines on how to configure your service to run mdBook.
     6‚ÜíSpecific recipes can be found at the [Automated Deployment] wiki page.
     7‚Üí
     8‚Üí[GitHub Actions]: https://docs.github.com/en/actions
     9‚Üí[GitLab CI/CD]: https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/ci/
    10‚Üí[Automated Deployment]: https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/wiki/Automated-Deployment
    11‚Üí
    12‚Üí## Installing mdBook
    14‚ÜíThere are several different strategies for installing mdBook.
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    17‚Üí### Pre-compiled binaries ‚Ä¶
    39‚Üí### Building from source ‚Ä¶
    67‚Üí## Running tests
    69‚ÜíYou may want to run tests using [`mdbook test`] every time you push a change or create a pull request.
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    83‚Üí## Deploying
    85‚ÜíYou may want to automatically deploy your book.
